\subsubsection{Fine-tuning}
We use the pre-trained ResNet-18 backbone to initialize the model, and then fine-tune it on the training set.
We use the Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) optimizer with momentum 0.9, weight decay 0.0005, and initial learning rate 0.001.
We use a cosine annealing learning rate scheduler with a maximum epoch of 100.
During training, we use the Cross-Entropy loss function.

\subsubsection{Post-processing}
After the classification, we apply a non-maximum suppression (NMS) with a threshold of 0.3 to remove the redundant detections.

